	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There is also Doppelganger's SMB2j disassembly, which can be used to remake the cartridge conversion by loopy,<br /><br />Other than modifying it to:<br /><br />- Moving stuff around for proper bank usage<br />- Optimize ROM and RAM usage (Removing unneeded/unused content)<br />- Remove (and replace if nessicary) FDS-specific registers<br />- redoing the IRQ routine or re-add sprite 0<br />- Seperate both the sound engines<br />- Move the parts of PRG that save to the RAM use $6000-7FFF (Battery Save RAM)<br />- Convert the CHR to ROM<br />... and other stuff<br /><br />It is possible to use MMC1 or MMC3 to do a port

		

		</td>
